[Malaria is endemic in many parts of India, but Goa is regarded as a low endemic area. In the newswire, it is alluded to that "the septic tanks here have become breeding grounds." Anopheles mosquitoes usually prefer clear water, and it is not certain that the mosquitoes breeding in the septic tanks are anopheles.

To understand the situation, it is important to know whether the inmates are from malaria endemic areas of India and thus could be a reservoir for local transmission.

A map of malaria in India can be found in the 2014, WHO World Malaria Report at http://www.who.int/malaria/publications/world_malaria_report_2014/wmr-2014-profiles.pdf?ua=1. - Mod.EP

HealthMap/ProMED-mail maps can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3676953,301, https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3676953,142.]
